      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:1:131:6",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) إِنَّ الْفُحْشَ لَوْ كَانَ مِثَالًا لَكَانَ مِثَالَ سَوْءٍ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Ibn Azina, from Zurara, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘If the immorality had a resemblance, its resemblance would be evil’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "6. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from ibn ‘Udhaynah from Zurara from abu Ja’far (a.s.) who has said the following: “The Messenger of Allah has said, ‘If obscene language had a form and shape it would have been a very ugly one.”’ "
        ]
      }
    }
